# Casual cover message style

Cover / stego carrier text should read like casual conversation discussing random everyday things, not polished small talk.

When editing prompts (`chain_system`, `prompt`, `carrierReplyInstruction`, semantic judge, sentence refresh):

- Prefer texting vibe: contractions, half-thoughts, everyday slang
- Broaden topics beyond day/weather/work (shows, games, food, errands, weird observations, weekend plans, opinions, pets, shopping, etc.)
- Allow mild topic drift inside one bubble; reject only abrupt nonsense
- Keep opener variety and same-sender continuation coherence rules
- Update `conversation-stenography.local.json` when changing defaults so local runs match
- Peers must share the same generative prompt config or decode breaks
